=# Repurpose Content to Social Posts

## Platform
{{ JSON.parse($('set_platform_examples').item.json.platform_config).name }}

## Platform Rules
- Character limit: {{ JSON.parse($('set_platform_examples').item.json.platform_config).charLimit }}
- Format: {{ JSON.parse($('set_platform_examples').item.json.platform_config).format }}

## Source Content
{{ $('workflow_trigger').item.json.content }}

## Writing Prime Directive
Write like a human, not a machine. Use clear, everyday language and short sentences. Cut cliches — no 'revolutionize,' 'game-changing,' 'unleash,' or 'delve.' Get to the point — remove filler words. No hype, just facts. Be genuine — don't fake excitement. Show, don't tell — use concrete examples instead of vague claims. Keep it tight and natural. Write like you'd text a smart friend.

## Output
Return a JSON object with a 'posts' array. Each post has 'text' and 'hashtags' (array without #).

parameters.jsCode:
const posts = $input.first().json.output?.posts || [];
const platform = $('workflow_trigger').item.json.platform || 'social';

const html = posts.map((p, i) => {
  const tags = (p.hashtags || []).map(h => `#${h}`).join(' ');
  return `<div style="background:#f5f5f5;border-left:4px solid #333;padding:12px 16px;margin:12px 0;border-radius:4px;">
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.5;margin:0 0 8px 0;white-space:pre-wrap;">${p.text}</p>
    ${tags ? `<p style="color:#1a73e8;font-size:13px;margin:0;">${tags}</p>` : ''}
  </div>`;
}).join('');

const result = posts.map(p => {
  const tags = (p.hashtags || []).map(h => `#${h}`).join(' ');
  return p.text + (tags ? '\n' + tags : '');
}).join('\n\n---\n\n');

return [{ json: { result, html, platform } }];

